Troops of Operation Thunder Strike, under the ongoing Operation ACCORD, had on 25 June 2020 foiled an attempted kidnap of passengers along the Abuja-Kaduna expressway by armed bandits. The coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche, said following actionable Human Intelligence on the activities of armed bandits between Olams and Alheri camps along the Abuja-Kaduna expressway, the troops promptly deployed to the scene and engaged the bandits with effective firepower. He said the troops overwhelmed the criminals forcing them to abandon their heinous mission and fled into the forest in disarray. He noted that as the troops engaged the bandits, passengers in the targeted vehicle, a Toyota Hiace Bus with registration number Lagos MUS-944FR travelling from Abuja to Kaduna, managed to escape in various directions into the surrounding bushes. However, troops pursued the bandits deep into the forest and inflicted fatal injuries on them, while also exhibiting the requisite composure in recovering all the passengers who escaped into the bush during the encounter. He said that all passengers in the targeted vehicle have been accounted for, adding that the troops are  exploiting the general area of the incident in search of the fleeing bandits, with express orders to bring them into custody,  while aggressive  patrols also are underway along the axis. 